        <abstract>
            <p>His answer to Asa Gray.</p>
            <p>On JDH’s view of aristocracy. Primogeniture is dreadfully opposed to selection.</p>
            <p>Orchid book proofs ready soon – has no idea whether it is worth publishing.</p>
            <p>Huxley on Owen.</p> 
<p>Feeble letter from J. H. Balfour against Huxley’s lectures ["Relation of man to lower animals", pt 2 of <hi rend="italic">Man’s place in nature</hi> (1863)].</p>  
<p>Has received the "astounding" <hi rend="italic">Angraecum sesquipedale</hi> with nectary 1ft long: "what insect could suck it?"</p> 
        </abstract>
